Gather is one of my go-to spots for healthy, gluten-free take-out in Park Slope. I'm a huge fan of the summer market bowl topped with their Moroccan spiced carrot slaw. The rotating daily selection of gluten-free, vegan muffins is incredible -- the best I've ever had! The staff is always very friendly, too.

Food is decent, service was bad enough to prevent me from coming back again. I have a few dietary restrictions, and the labeling and staff communication around ingredients was non-existent.  When I arrived I was trying to figure out what the bakery items were, as there was no labels or listing. The cashier looked annoyed and asked what I wanted. I said I wasn't sure what everything was. She said there were labels but she didn't put them out (like this was my fault). I asked about the ingredients in a court things and when she mentioned scallions in one I made it clear I couldn't eat scallions or any alliums.  Again this was met with great annoyance by the cashier.  I eventually got the avocado toast, which turned out to be mixed with a ton of chives (also an allium). This wasn't mentioned at all on the menu, or by the cashier. Because we were doing takeout I didn't realize this until home when it was too late to do anything. Since chives are not a non-standard ingredient in avocado toast I hadn't thought to ask when ordering.  Request to management: Please consider labeling dishes with sensitive ingredients and allergens going forward.
Amazing food, always has been fresh, and very clean tasting. Their vegan gluten free muffin was so delicious!
Great coffee and great service
I’ve been getting lunch here 1-2 times per week for the last several months. The food is delicious and healthy. Really happy to have them as an option when I don’t have time to pack lunch.

Did I spend $17 on a single dish, not including tip? Yes. Was it absolutely delicious, refreshing, filling but didn’t leave me feeling lethargic? Also yes. The kale salad was to die for, big thanks to the counter girl for suggesting it! The chicken breast was great and very high quality. If I could afford it, I would make it here more than once a week. I can’t wait to try out more of the menu.
This place is perfect for me. Love the menu and turmeric latte
Overpriced Brooklyn café with no distinguishing features
Great coffee, great cakes, muffins and scoons. A place to take into account is you want to relax a bit, take a hot drink, have a calm talk with a friend.
Been going here for a few years, best healthy food, best baked goods, wonderful staff. We love Gather.
Yummmm!! It says health food, but there’s plenty of sweets and delicious things that seem way too tasty to be categorized as health food, even if it is good for you.
Overpriced

This place has its own look and vibe, it is different, but their coffee isn’t something special, lack in taste, I was expecting a rich in flavor coffee , but maybe its me, because I was expecting more from place like this.
Baked goods are absolutely delicious. I love how the selection is different every time you go in.
This could be the kind of place I'd hate, but it's not. Food even a carnivore could endure and be almost happy, and nice people.
Ordered just one garden bowl and it never arrived. Whoever runs the delivery here is not doing a good job at all. Nothing is worth over an hour and a half wait time. DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE.

Food, coffee, and desserts. Food menu is limited, but what they do offer is good. They have "no laptop hours" during busy times (see picture). Nice atmosphere, and I'd like to try the brunch.

First of all, the coffee is done right. Great espresso from a local roaster. What brings Gather from good to great, though, is the food. It’s all homemade and so delicious even though they have such a casual vibe. Love it!

I went to this place basically 3 out of the 4 days I was in Brooklyn. Walked from my AirBnb  to Gather, bought my beverage and pastry, and I sat near the window where I can see people walking by (and their dogs!).  I could have walked to the coffee shop that was much closer to where I was staying, but I loved the atmosphere of Gather that I had to go back again, and again. I hope to be back someday.
Had the summer bowl and the vegan options were fantastic. The only reason I'm withholding 5 stars is because the seasonal veggies were both cold and oily. Best hummus I've ever had, though.
Great coffee shop with a bright and clean atmosphere. Delicious, healthy food with a nice lunch special- soup and side for $11. Kid friendly too.

Excellent coffee, baked goods, and food. The avocado and egg sandwiches are worth a trip alone (get there early though because they sell out fast). The staff is always friendly and welcoming as well. I only wished the would label all of their baked good options, so you don’t have to ask what everything is.
Friendly and knowledgeable barista. I got their “best mocha in the world” and it was quite good.

Trendy little spot for freelancers w/ laptops, food is a bit pricy, but dude, it’s sooooo good, especially if you want to eat healthy. Best WiFi cafe food EVER. Not the friendliest staff, but it’s fine. They’re courteous enough.

A good choice if you are looking for a place with delicious healthy options. They offer a weekend brunch menu. I saw gluten free and vegan options as well. Credit cards, debit cards, and cash accepted. Wheelchair accessible entrance and seating. A few tables to eat in and take out also available. Street parking only (no parking lot or structure). Right next to the F/G trains and the B67 & B69 bus stop.

This is my favorite cafe in Park Slope. Cozy seat, delicious foods and coffee. They also have brunch menu in weekend. I tried mushroom omelette and it was so delicious. Also kale salad from regular menu is also my favorite. WiFi is available and it’s stable.

Eh, weak coffee, strangely frenetic service, decent food, uncomfortable seats - overall not nearly as good or interesting as it thinks it is.

One of my personal favorite coffee shops in Park Slope. Good seating, good espresso. Not usually too busy to find a place to sit. Their mocha really is excellent and hard to beat. If you like mochas, I wouldn't miss theirs.
